      "side": 1,
      "message": "https://source.chromium.org/chromium/infra/infra/+/master:go/src/go.chromium.org/luci/logdog/api/logpb/log.proto;l\u003d86-89\n\nThe protocol allows an entry to contain only 0 or 1 partial lines. If len(lines) \u003e 1, it can\u0027t contain a partial line. Thus, the choice of lines[len(lines) - 1] vs lines[0] is the choice of how this handles invalid input data.\n\nThe current logic consider all the lines as complete ones, if len(lines) \u003e 0.\nI put L207 and L208 to explain the constraint, but maybe not intuitive enough?",
      "parentUuid": "ccb2a17c_bc984a3a",
